    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-20T10:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-20T10:25:00-05:00" n="51"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3963: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-20T18:00:00+02:35"
                            >March 20, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>170. Have just received <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> from Ethiopian
                    Foreign Office dated today protesting formally against constant violation by
                    Italy of article XXIII (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) and article XXV of Hague
                    Convention No. 4 of 1907<note n="20" xml:id="d51fn20">
                        <ref target="frus1907p2#pg_1204">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1907, pt. 2, p.
                        1204</ref>.</note> and Geneva Protocol of June 17, 1925,<note n="21"
                        xml:id="d51fn21">
                        <ref target="frus1925v01#pg_89">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, 1925, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            89</ref>.</note> by using asphyxiating gases and bombing civilian
                    populations.</p>
                <p>Ethiopian Government reserves all rights under article III of said Hague
                    Convention and appeals to the Government of the United States as one of the
                    signatories of the above-mentioned convention and protocol “to be good enough to
                    take all measure it may deem proper to cause the enemy to desist immediately
                    from the said violations.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
